I Loved this movie.  Karen Abercrombie (Suzzane Waters)  and  T.C. Stallings (David Waters)  are very good in this movie.  But most of all I liked the story behind this movie.  Trusting Gods direction, Suzzane's North becomes clear as she takes in a delinquent teenager, Eli. Trusting God, she puts her home up for his bail and has him come live with her. And soon discovers he has a little sister who is missing, whom he loves very much. Some young people have it hard, I know because I can identify with this movie, being in foster care myself.  But I can tell you this movie is very uplifting and so worth watching.
I very much want this product and I am very disappointed that it wasn't delivered when I was told it would be.

Excellent! This is a movie that the entire family can watch together. It shows God's love, mercy and grace. It also shows how we (inhabitants on this earth) are connected to each other more than we realize.

If you loved War Room, don't expect the same from this movie.  Karen Abercrombie is great.  The plot is reasonable and the movie could have been much better with the right cast.  TC Stallings' acting took this movie down.  I look for good Christian movies.  This one fit the genre, but just didn't live up to expectations.

Thoroughly enjoyed this movie.  We have an adopted older child and she cried as she watched this especially at the end.

I was very dissapointed with this movie. I was really hoping that it was going to be better. I love the actors in all of their other films. The movie is not even close to being as good as War Room. I do appreciate the effort at a Christian film. I do feel that I wasted my money. Part of the storyline was just strange as the main character struggles to get over her husband's death. She speaks to her dead husband several times in the movie. As a Christian, I don't believe we should be talking to the dead. Also, the music in the film is not Christian. There is no bad language and it is safe to watch around children. The storyline was not realistic and the acting was not the best. Some parts of the move just didn't flow well either. I love to support Christian movies and so sorry that I must leave a not so favorable review.  Yet, I'm obligated to be honest. I expected better from these actors after seeing War Room.

Really sad to write this but this was a serious disappointment. I love to buy Christian movies and support the people making them but this one just doesn't make the cut. The acting is bad, which I could live with if it had a great message, but it doesn't even really have that. The story is convoluted and there are parts that I am not even sure why they are there because they don't add anything to the story. The only thing it has going for it is that my kids can watch it over and over if they want (which is in doubt)because it is a Christian movie and so it doesn't have any bad messages- and does at least have a positive family theme-
Neat idea having all the intertwining stories. I like how it ended.

Gods Compass is an uplifting and powerfully poignant story that reminds us all of the importance of following our true north callings in life.  Gods Compass is an encouraging and inspirational story for the whole family. DN
A heartwarming story for the entire family. If you like to feel challenged and uplifted after watching a movie, get God's compass.

This is a terrific movie for all ages with great writing and directing. The cast stars Karen Abercrombie and T.C. Stallings from War Room and tells an inspirational story about finding your true North in life. Great production value while really making the viewer think about what's important in life. A great gift idea for that special person in your life.
